      <h2>Flow collision notes for fashion teams</h2>
      <p>Fashion stores run more concurrent automations than most verticals — drops, waitlists, cart recovery, post-purchase fit education, seasonal winback, and site-wide sale campaigns. Without a collision calendar, Shopify email marketing apps become noise machines.</p>
      <p><strong>Drop week:</strong> Pause cart recovery discount escalation. Suppress welcome promos for anyone who joined via drop landing page in last 72 hours — they already have intent. VIP early-access must exclude public sale segments entirely.</p>
      <p><strong>Clearance week:</strong> Pause winback flows offering full-price framing. Post-purchase education for recent buyers should suppress clearance blasts — nothing erodes trust like "loved your order" Monday and "everything 40% off" Tuesday.</p>
